## Mission: Give the kids what they need to be successful in school (K-12).

## Problem:  
# Students don't feel safe at school
# Parents don't feel their children are safe at school
# Children need nourishment at school, regardless of parental income
# Teachers should not have to police students or protect students from domestic terrorists
# Teachers are not provided with the tools they need to be successful with their students

## ##
## Requirements ##
# Students and Teachers should feel safe at school.
# Kids should get what they need to be successful in school.
# Teachers should have the tools they need to be successful.
# Students should have access to a variety of skill building courses.
# Stop making the exceptions become the rules. Accomodate exceptions, but hold fast to the rules.
# Kids perform better when they feel they must play by same rules as the other kids.
## ##

### Health/nutrition ###
  # Daily nutritional lunch provided regardless of parental income. 
  # Parents and the community can volunteer/sponsor. Those funds can offset costs.
  # Students can opt out of the free lunch or pay for their own.

### Safety/Security ###
  # Kids and Teachers need to feel safe at school. 
  # Teachers should not have to police students or strangers.
  # Police presence needed for safety and security for our students and teachers.

### Support Teachers ###
  # Give teachers the tools they need to be successful.

### Promote Skills ###
  # Academics (math, science, history, language arts)
  # Art
  # Music
  # Economics
  # Civics (policy, government)
  # Computer Science and STEM
  # Craft skills
  # Mechanical skills

### Opportunities ###
  # Maintain communications with alumni and local community. 
  # Opportunity for continuous learning.
  # Help students find jobs.

### Policy Recommendations: Education ###

# Give students and teachers in public education what they need to be successful:
    # Safety/Security - Students and Teachers should feel safe in school. Police presence is needed.
    # Health/nutrition - Daily nutritional lunch provided for free. 
    # Support Teachers - Give teachers the tools they need to be successful.
    # Promote Skills - 
              # Academics (math, science, history, language arts)
              # Art
              # Music
              # Economics
              # Civics (policy, government)
              # Computer Science and STEM
              # Craft skills
              # Mechanical skills
    # Opportunities - Support current students, alumni, and the community with opportunities for continuous learning.

### Budget ###
            # Budget unknown.
            # We will find the money because education is priority number 1.

### Measure Success ###
# Surveys
            # Do children feel safe at school
            # Do parents feel their children are safe at school
# Trade school and college enrollment
# Careers - unemployment rates of graduates six months after graduation
